So I've been thinking about this , Idea came from the fact when I tried to give different personalities to agent there wasn't any organized collection that I can allow agent to use.

A soul is just a file that gives an agent a real personality.

I had to create a unique soul every time , I wanted different personality and it was annoying and time taking , so I created dedicated repo where we collectively make souls test them and push it. so we can have 100s of souls that we can use anytime.

Right now the repo has five souls:

* **Jarvis**
* **Gojo**
* **Eren Yeager**
* **René Descartes**
* **Rapper**

Each one was written with real care. We dug by researching about each personality on internet, how this personality speaks , what words they use , how they speak and think , what there political believe etc you can check out more instructions in repo.

Here's the repo:
https://github.com/madhvantyagi/SOUL.md

And honestly this is where you come in. I don't want this to be my little project. I want it to be a library of souls that people actually want to use. So if there's a character, a thinker, a vibe, a voice you love, write a soul for it and send it over. The only rule is make it real. Give it a personality someone would pick on purpose, not another generic assistant.

Come build some souls with me. I really want to see what you all come up with.